1
00:00:15,724 --> 00:00:17,016
DIRECTOR:
Quiet on the set.

2
00:00:17,184 --> 00:00:18,226
[BELL RINGS]

3
00:00:18,394 --> 00:00:21,229
WOMAN: Okay, everybody, quiet on the set.
MAN: Scene 1, Take 10, marker.

4
00:00:24,274 --> 00:00:25,775
[PHONE RINGING]

5
00:00:27,945 --> 00:00:31,155
DIRECTOR:
And action.

6
00:00:32,991 --> 00:00:34,617
Joel Levison's office.

7
00:00:34,827 --> 00:00:38,121
No, I'm sorry, he's not in yet.
May I take a message?

8
00:00:38,372 --> 00:00:40,998
- Yes, I'll tell him you called.
- Sandy, never say that.

9
00:00:41,208 --> 00:00:44,377
He's either in conference, in a meeting.
He's always in.

10
00:00:44,628 --> 00:00:47,630
- Now, who was that?
- A Larry Levy?

11
00:00:48,298 --> 00:00:50,550
I hope there was nothing
in the trades. Was there?

12
00:00:50,759 --> 00:00:52,176
I don't know. The mail's late.

13
00:00:52,386 --> 00:00:54,470
- Well, go get them. Now!
- Yes, ma'am.

14
00:00:54,638 --> 00:00:57,849
I want them back here
before he arrives.

15
00:01:12,656 --> 00:01:14,699
ADAM:
Griffin. Griffin, hi.

16
00:01:14,908 --> 00:01:17,827
Adam Simon. I know we're
not supposed to meet till next week...

17
00:01:17,995 --> 00:01:20,538
...but a lot of heat...
- Didn't realize we were meeting.

18
00:01:20,706 --> 00:01:23,207
I wanted to plant the seed
in your head just so that...

19
00:01:23,417 --> 00:01:25,126
I'm booked up. I can't hear a pitch.

20
00:01:25,294 --> 00:01:28,421
Picture this. It's a planet in
the far, far future with two suns.

21
00:01:28,589 --> 00:01:30,840
- Who plays the sons?
- No, suns. Large solar disks.

22
00:01:31,008 --> 00:01:32,884
You gotta run this idea
by Bonnie Sherow.

23
00:01:33,051 --> 00:01:36,220
Pictures they make these days
are all MTV. Cut, cut, cut, cut.

24
00:01:36,388 --> 00:01:40,016
The opening shot of Welles' Touch of Evil
was six and a half minutes long.

25
00:01:40,184 --> 00:01:41,392
Six and a half minutes, Walter?

26
00:01:41,602 --> 00:01:45,688
Well, three or four. Anyway, he set up the
whole picture with that one tracking shot.

27
00:01:45,856 --> 00:01:48,065
My father was the key grip on that shoot.

28
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:52,236
Hey, what about Absolute Beginners?
Man, that was an extraordinary shot.

29
00:01:52,404 --> 00:01:55,740
- What was that? Never heard of it.
- Julien Temple. It's an English film.

30
00:01:55,908 --> 00:01:58,201
GRIFFIN: Morning.
- We're talking about American movies...

31
00:01:58,368 --> 00:01:59,911
...and Orson Welles was a master.

32
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:03,039
GRIFFIN: Can I have a Pellegrino, please?
JAN: I've got Calistoga.

33
00:02:03,207 --> 00:02:05,291
GRIFFIN: Hi, Buck, how are you?
- Good, how you doing?

34
00:02:05,459 --> 00:02:09,712
GRIFFIN: Good. What do you got for me?
- Okay, here it is.

35
00:02:09,880 --> 00:02:12,715
- The Graduate Part Two.
- Oh, good, good.

36
00:02:12,883 --> 00:02:15,718
Now, listen.
The three principals are still with us.

37
00:02:15,886 --> 00:02:18,888
Dustin Hoffman, Anne Bancroft,
Katharine Ross.

38
00:02:19,056 --> 00:02:20,056
GRIFFIN:
Mm-hm.

39
00:02:20,224 --> 00:02:23,559
Twenty-five years later,
and so are the characters.

40
00:02:23,769 --> 00:02:26,395
Ben, Elaine and Mrs. Robinson.

41
00:02:26,605 --> 00:02:28,397
Ben and Elaine are married still.

42
00:02:28,565 --> 00:02:33,027
They live in a big, old, spooky house
up in northern California somewhere...

43
00:02:33,237 --> 00:02:35,738
...and Mrs. Robinson lives with them.

44
00:02:35,906 --> 00:02:40,243
GRIFFIN: Mm.
- Her aging mother, who's had a stroke...

45
00:02:40,410 --> 00:02:42,954
- Mrs. Robinson's had a stroke?
- Had a stroke, so she can't talk.

46
00:02:43,121 --> 00:02:44,956
- Is this gonna be funny?
- Yeah, it'll be funny.

47
00:02:45,123 --> 00:02:47,458
Dark, and weird, and funny
and with a stroke.

48
00:02:47,626 --> 00:02:49,168
- Okay.
- Maybe it's not a stroke.

49
00:02:49,378 --> 00:02:51,504
- Maybe it's... I don't know what it is.
- Anyway, go on.

50
00:02:51,672 --> 00:02:53,005
- It's a malady of some sort.
- Okay.

51
00:02:53,173 --> 00:02:56,425
She's up there in the bedroom upstairs,
listening to everything that happens.

52
00:02:56,593 --> 00:02:59,303
They've got a daughter
who's just graduated from college.

53
00:02:59,513 --> 00:03:01,764
- Young blood.
- Twenty-two, 23-year-old.

54
00:03:01,932 --> 00:03:03,641
- Like a Julia Roberts.
- Julia Roberts. Great.

55
00:03:03,851 --> 00:03:04,934
JAN: Excuse me.
- Yes?

56
00:03:05,102 --> 00:03:08,062
- What do I do with these scripts?
- Uh, that goes to Bonnie Sherow.

57
00:03:08,230 --> 00:03:11,399
And, uh, find out from studio security
how Adam Simon got on the lot.

58
00:03:11,567 --> 00:03:14,443
- I wanna know.
- Okay. Adam Simon? Okay.

59
00:03:14,611 --> 00:03:16,779
- Okay? Julia Roberts comes home.
- Yes, go ahead.

60
00:03:16,947 --> 00:03:18,364
Their daughter, the graduate.

61
00:03:18,532 --> 00:03:20,700
- And she brings her...
- The new graduate.

62
00:03:20,868 --> 00:03:23,077
ADAM: Griffin loved it.
He wanted me to run it by you.

63
00:03:23,245 --> 00:03:26,372
A band of human survivors,
generations removed from the mother ship.

64
00:03:26,540 --> 00:03:29,208
They have no history.
They've lost their technological knowledge.

65
00:03:29,376 --> 00:03:31,878
I can't process this.
Could you write it down?

66
00:03:32,045 --> 00:03:33,713
It's not about words, it's about pictures.

67
00:03:33,881 --> 00:03:34,922
[JIMMY YELLS]

68
00:03:35,090 --> 00:03:36,132
[CRASH]

69
00:03:36,300 --> 00:03:37,425
- Oh, my God.
- Oh, man.

70
00:03:38,385 --> 00:03:41,304
Jimmy? Jimmy, are you okay?

71
00:03:41,513 --> 00:03:43,848
- What happened?
JIMMY: Twenty-five words or less?

72
00:03:44,057 --> 00:03:45,099
BONNIE:
Are you all right?

73
00:03:45,267 --> 00:03:47,101
JIMMY:
I'd like to say, my name is Jimmy Chase.

74
00:03:47,269 --> 00:03:49,312
BONNIE:
You all right? Open your eyes. You okay?

75
00:03:49,479 --> 00:03:52,023
DRIVER: He just came out of nowhere,
ran right into the car.

76
00:03:52,190 --> 00:03:54,400
BONNIE: Take it slow.
ADAM: It's okay.

77
00:03:55,777 --> 00:03:57,194
Yeah, it's okay.

78
00:03:57,362 --> 00:03:59,113
JIMMY:
Hey. Hey, that's Adam Simon.

79
00:03:59,281 --> 00:04:01,407
ADAM:
How you doing, kid? I just had a meeting.

80
00:04:01,575 --> 00:04:03,159
BONNIE: You all right?
ADAM: It was good.

81
00:04:03,327 --> 00:04:05,244
JIMMY: Yeah, yeah.
BONNIE: You sure you're okay?

82
00:04:09,917 --> 00:04:12,710
REG: Rebecca De Mornay.
Actually, you're much better looking.

83
00:04:12,878 --> 00:04:14,795
STEVE: As a matter of fact, we...
WOMAN: Um, no.

84
00:04:14,963 --> 00:04:16,672
- I'm not Rebecca De Mornay.
REG: Dead ringer.

85
00:04:16,840 --> 00:04:18,090
Thank you. Thank you very much.

86
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:20,801
REG:
You know where Joel Levison's office is?

87
00:04:20,969 --> 00:04:23,554
WOMAN:
The Mr. Levison, head of the studio? Yeah.

88
00:04:23,722 --> 00:04:25,973
STEVE: But it's quite moving.
It'll rip your heart out.

89
00:04:26,141 --> 00:04:30,478
This is the area where we make decisions
to give a green light to a picture like that.

90
00:04:30,646 --> 00:04:33,397
Right here. We're gonna go
about 17 stories high, if we can.

91
00:04:33,565 --> 00:04:38,194
We're gonna continue using Sony products.
Domo arigato to the Sony products, really.

92
00:04:38,403 --> 00:04:41,197
In fact, if you need someone
to eat some sashimi with you...

93
00:04:41,406 --> 00:04:42,949
...you give me a ring because...

94
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:45,034
- Levison's right here.
BONNIE: Write it down.

95
00:04:45,202 --> 00:04:47,954
ADAM:
I have to know that you're just seeing it.

96
00:04:48,580 --> 00:04:49,622
CELIA:
Good girl.

97
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:51,540
LEVISON:
Traffic from Malibu was impossible.

98
00:04:51,708 --> 00:04:53,501
CELIA: Morning, Joel.
LEVISON: Morning, Celia.

99
00:04:53,669 --> 00:04:55,461
- Sandy, park the car, please.
SANDY: Okay.

100
00:04:55,629 --> 00:04:57,421
LEVISON: Morning, Marty.
MARTY: Morning, Joel.

101
00:04:57,589 --> 00:04:58,965
CELIA:
Hi.

102
00:04:59,508 --> 00:05:03,928
MARTY: What are the Japs doing here?
- So, what's this talk about heads will roll?

103
00:05:04,096 --> 00:05:05,846
The bank's putting the screws to us.

104
00:05:06,014 --> 00:05:08,557
Harvey Goldman's son's coming out,
and I don't like it.

105
00:05:08,767 --> 00:05:12,436
Reggie Goldman's a pipsqueak.
You can't be serious.

106
00:05:12,646 --> 00:05:15,564
You know, some changes
are going on around here.

107
00:05:15,732 --> 00:05:19,568
It's always the way.
Happened at Paramount three years ago.

108
00:05:19,736 --> 00:05:21,612
Columbia's going through it now.

109
00:05:21,822 --> 00:05:23,906
I hear we're looking to replace Griffin.

110
00:05:24,116 --> 00:05:26,617
Griffin? I don't believe it. With who?

111
00:05:26,827 --> 00:05:28,744
MARTY:
Berg, Kirkpatrick. Maybe Larry Levy.

112
00:05:28,912 --> 00:05:33,624
Yeah. Yeah, well, I wanna know why
the security is so lax, that's why.

113
00:05:33,834 --> 00:05:36,711
I'll talk to you about it later.
I'm in the middle of a pitch.

114
00:05:36,878 --> 00:05:38,921
- Listen. Go ahead.
- Yeah, okay, okay.

115
00:05:39,089 --> 00:05:41,924
It's a TV star and she goes on safari
in Africa.

116
00:05:42,092 --> 00:05:44,427
You're talking about a TV star
in a motion picture?

117
00:05:44,594 --> 00:05:47,138
Not a real TV star.
It would be played by a movie star.

118
00:05:47,305 --> 00:05:50,725
- A movie star playing a television star.
- Goldie, Julia, Michelle...

119
00:05:50,934 --> 00:05:52,435
...Bette, Lily.
- Dolly Parton.

120
00:05:52,602 --> 00:05:54,478
PARTICIA: Dolly.
JOAN: She would be very good.

121
00:05:54,688 --> 00:05:56,772
GRIFFIN: I like Goldie.
JOAN: Goldie Goes to Africa.

122
00:05:56,940 --> 00:05:58,149
Great. We have a relationship.

123
00:05:58,316 --> 00:06:01,485
- That would be great. Goldie Goes to Africa.
- Goldie Goes to Africa.

124
00:06:01,653 --> 00:06:03,612
JOAN: She becomes worshiped.
GRIFFIN: Worshiped?

125
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:05,781
- Well, she's found by this tribe...
GRIFFIN: Yes?

126
00:06:05,949 --> 00:06:07,742
Of small people. But then she has to...

127
00:06:07,909 --> 00:06:10,578
She's found by this tribe
and they worship her. But then...

128
00:06:10,746 --> 00:06:12,872
GRIFFIN:
I see. It's like a Gods Must Be Crazy...

129
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:15,124
...except the Coke bottle's
now a television actress.

130
00:06:15,292 --> 00:06:17,752
Yeah, exactly right.
It's Out of Africa meets Pretty Woman.

131
00:06:17,919 --> 00:06:19,336
And she has to decide...

132
00:06:19,504 --> 00:06:23,382
...whether to stay with the TV show
or save this entire African tribe.

133
00:06:23,592 --> 00:06:24,633
JOAN:
It could be a man.

134
00:06:24,801 --> 00:06:27,053
Hey, where's Griffin Mill's office?
JIMMY: Right here.

135
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:30,264
- Hey, you're Martin Scorsese.
ALAN: No, but I know Harvey Keitel.

136
00:06:30,432 --> 00:06:33,976
Yeah, I know you do.
Hey, I loved Cape Fear. Ha, ha.

137
00:06:34,144 --> 00:06:36,479
- My old man worked for Hitchcock too.
- Yeah?

138
00:06:36,688 --> 00:06:40,274
Rope. It was a masterpiece.
The story wasn't any good.

139
00:06:40,442 --> 00:06:43,569
He shot the whole thing without cuts.
I hate all this cut, cut, cut.

140
00:06:43,737 --> 00:06:47,239
Oh, yeah, well, what about, uh, Bertolucci,
that great tracking shot...

141
00:06:47,491 --> 00:06:51,202
...with Winger in Sheltering Sky?
- I didn't see it.

142
00:06:52,621 --> 00:06:54,830
Touch of Evil, that was the one.
Welles...

143
00:06:54,998 --> 00:06:56,916
WHITNEY:
I been here since 8:00. Honest I have.

144
00:06:57,084 --> 00:07:00,002
I stuck my neck out for you to get this job.
Who were you with?

145
00:07:00,170 --> 00:07:04,256
- I was there with, um, Alan Rudolph.
- What were you doing with Alan Rudolph?

146
00:07:04,424 --> 00:07:07,593
Well, no, he asked me to have coffee.
He was telling me this idea.

147
00:07:07,761 --> 00:07:09,470
- What do I say?
- You're my assistant.

148
00:07:09,638 --> 00:07:13,307
- Don't get involved with writers.
- I wasn't. I was just listening to this idea.

149
00:07:13,475 --> 00:07:16,102
- I told him he should give it to you.
GRIFFIN: What's your pitch?

150
00:07:16,269 --> 00:07:17,937
Well, does political scare you?

151
00:07:18,146 --> 00:07:21,190
GRIFFIN: Political doesn't scare me.
Radical political scares me.

152
00:07:21,358 --> 00:07:24,693
- "Political" political scares me.
- This is politely politically radical.

153
00:07:24,861 --> 00:07:26,070
- Is it funny?
- It's funny.

154
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:28,405
- It's a funny political thing.
- It's a thriller too.

155
00:07:28,615 --> 00:07:30,282
- It's a thriller?
- All at once.

156
00:07:30,534 --> 00:07:31,784
So, uh, what's the story?

157
00:07:32,035 --> 00:07:34,328
Well, I want Bruce Willis.
I think I can talk to him.

158
00:07:34,496 --> 00:07:37,957
Um, it's a story about a senator.
A bad-guy senator at first.

159
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:40,793
He's traveling around the country
on the country's dime.

160
00:07:40,961 --> 00:07:45,047
- Like that Sununu guy used to do.
- Sort of a cynical, political thriller-comedy?

161
00:07:45,257 --> 00:07:47,466
Yeah, but it's got a heart, uh,
in the right spot.

162
00:07:47,676 --> 00:07:50,136
And anyway, he has an accident.

163
00:07:50,345 --> 00:07:53,430
- An accident?
- Yeah, and he becomes clairvoyant.

164
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:55,266
- Like a psychic. Yeah.
- Oh, I see.

165
00:07:55,475 --> 00:07:58,602
So it's kind of a psychic, political
thriller-comedy with a heart.

166
00:07:58,812 --> 00:08:03,107
With a heart. And, uh, not unlike Ghost
meets Manchurian Candidate.

167
00:08:03,316 --> 00:08:06,193
- Go on, I'm listening.
- He can start to read people's minds...

168
00:08:06,361 --> 00:08:11,240
...and when he gets to the president's mind,
it's completely blank. Completely blank.

169
00:08:11,408 --> 00:08:13,701
JAN: Can I get you anything?
ALAN: I'd like a beer, please.

170
00:08:13,869 --> 00:08:17,580
JAN: We don't have beer.
ALAN: Uh, wine. Red wine, please.

171
00:08:18,456 --> 00:08:22,293
Of course, someone gets killed at the end.
They always do in political thrillers.

172
00:08:22,460 --> 00:08:23,919
[PHONE RINGS]

173
00:08:24,087 --> 00:08:25,087
Griffin Mill's office.

174
00:08:25,255 --> 00:08:26,922
MAN [ON PHONE]:
I know. Can you put him on?

175
00:08:27,090 --> 00:08:29,633
GRIFFIN: It's an intriguing idea, Jim.
- May I ask who's calling?

176
00:08:29,801 --> 00:08:31,760
MAN [ON PHONE]:
I'd like to speak to Griffin Mill.

177
00:08:31,928 --> 00:08:34,305
JAN: He's in a meeting.
I'll have him get back to you.

178
00:08:34,472 --> 00:08:36,140
GRIFFIN: I'll get back to you.
JIM: Thanks.

179
00:08:36,308 --> 00:08:38,100
JAN: Excuse me, sir?
MAN [ON PHONE]: Bullshit.

180
00:08:38,268 --> 00:08:39,768
- He'll get back to me?
- Seen my Binaca?

181
00:08:39,936 --> 00:08:41,604
Do you know how many times
I've heard that?

182
00:08:41,771 --> 00:08:44,315
JAN: Who is this?
MAN: If he don't get back to me...

183
00:08:44,482 --> 00:08:46,108
BONNIE: I read that script.
- Who was that?

184
00:08:46,276 --> 00:08:47,568
JAN:
I don't know. He didn't say.

185
00:08:47,736 --> 00:08:50,696
- What do you mean, he didn't say?
BONNIE: How are you gonna cast it?

186
00:08:50,906 --> 00:08:53,866
The lead character is a 50-year-old
female circus performer.

187
00:08:54,034 --> 00:08:56,827
- A fire-eater.
- Let me read the coverage.

188
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:59,205
Are we still having lunch
with Aaron Camp?

189
00:08:59,372 --> 00:09:02,124
GRIFFIN: Yeah, what time?
- I made it for 1:00.

190
00:09:02,459 --> 00:09:04,835
- Bad day?
JAN: He's having writer's block.

191
00:09:07,130 --> 00:09:10,174
You have a meeting with Harders
and Frank South this afternoon.

192
00:09:10,342 --> 00:09:12,468
- What time? I'll be here.
- At 3:00. Okay.

193
00:09:12,636 --> 00:09:14,136
Put the meetings on the computer.

194
00:09:14,304 --> 00:09:16,138
- All right.
- Thanks.

195
00:09:16,306 --> 00:09:18,682
- You going now? I'll go with you.
- I'm going to see Levison.

196
00:09:18,850 --> 00:09:21,352
I'll meet you there.
Order me a salad and Crystal Geyser.

197
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:22,811
- Okay. Bye.
- Thanks.

198
00:09:22,979 --> 00:09:24,146
WOMAN:
Bonnie, can I please...?

199
00:09:24,314 --> 00:09:26,523
BONNIE:
We gotta have a time to meet. I'm sorry.

200
00:09:30,654 --> 00:09:33,822
- Okay, by 5? Thanks, Sandy.
- Bye.

201
00:09:33,990 --> 00:09:35,366
- Hi, Sandy. Hi, Celia.
- Oh, uh...

202
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:37,660
You can't go in there. He's in a meeting.

203
00:09:37,827 --> 00:09:40,371
REG: I think, you know,
dime a dozen out here, don't you?

204
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:42,915
- It's all right, Celia.
- You know this one?

205
00:09:43,083 --> 00:09:45,167
Griffin, I don't think
you've met Reg Goldman.

206
00:09:45,377 --> 00:09:48,712
- You know his father, Harvey.
- Yes, of course. Hi. Hi, Reg.

207
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:50,881
- Nice to meet you.
- From the bank in Boston.

208
00:09:51,049 --> 00:09:54,176
- Reg is out here for a couple of weeks.
- Great.

209
00:09:54,386 --> 00:09:58,013
- Business or pleasure?
- A little of both, I hope.

210
00:09:58,431 --> 00:10:01,058
Reg is thinking of getting
into production, Griffin.

211
00:10:01,268 --> 00:10:02,601
Oh, really?

212
00:10:02,811 --> 00:10:05,062
REG:
Yeah. It beats work, doesn't it, Griffin?

213
00:10:05,272 --> 00:10:07,523
Like to play some tennis though.
You play tennis?

214
00:10:07,732 --> 00:10:09,942
